article.headline: Virginia Commonwealth 88, William & Mary 77
article.story: WILLIAMSBURG, Va. (AP) -- Jesse Pellot-Rosa scored 15 of his 20 points in the second half Wednesday night and helped Virginia Commonwealth University withstand a challenge by William & Mary as the Rams won for the 11th time in 12 games, 88-77. The Rams (13-3, 5-0 Colonial Athletic Association) led 39-29 at halftime and saw the Tribe get within 61-58 with 7:25 to play. But VCU answered with a 10-3 run and the visitors remained ahead by at least eight the rest of the way. The Tribe (10-5, 3-2) had its seven-game winning streak snapped. Adam Payton led William & Mary with 26 points, Nathan Mann had 14 and Alex Smith scored 12. T.J. Gwynn led the Rams with 22 points and Eric Maynor added 19 and six assists. The Rams shot almost 60 percent and won their ninth straight in the series.
